docs.abstract: The paper, started by practitioners of Falun Gong, has turned to the video platform for an advertising blitz.
docs.snippet: The paper, started by practitioners of Falun Gong, has turned to the video platform for an advertising blitz.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Late last summer, YouTube users began noticing a surge of ads for an obscure news outlet called The Epoch Times. One ad touted an exposé of “Spygate,” a baseless conspiracy theory alleging that President Barack Obama and his allies placed a spy inside President Trump’s 2016 campaign. Another praised Mr. Trump’s interest in buying Greenland as a shrewd strategic move. A third claimed that the opioid epidemic in the United States was the result of a chemical warfare plot by the Chinese Communist Party.

headline.main: Epoch Times, Punished by Facebook, Gets a New Megaphone on YouTube
headline.print_headline: A Pro-Trump Voice Makes YouTube Its New Megaphone
